WEBVTT

00:00:28.288 --> 00:00:30.189
So welcome to this episode of the Yahweh

00:00:30.208 --> 00:00:30.568
Vlog.

00:00:30.868 --> 00:00:32.628
We're returning our attention to the

00:00:32.668 --> 00:00:35.170
series called Returning to the Garden.

00:00:35.850 --> 00:00:38.430
We are now at the point that Yahweh,

00:00:38.570 --> 00:00:41.892
after having chastised Hasatan, Satan,

00:00:41.932 --> 00:00:42.573
the serpent,

00:00:43.052 --> 00:00:45.893
he's turning his attention to the devil's

00:00:45.933 --> 00:00:48.594
little helpers because life would be more

00:00:48.655 --> 00:00:51.215
challenging for them and it would be quite

00:00:51.256 --> 00:00:52.176
different for them.

00:00:52.875 --> 00:00:56.238
She would do as they were, well,

00:00:56.279 --> 00:00:57.820
as she was originally designed,

00:00:57.859 --> 00:00:59.722
which would mean that she would be

00:00:59.781 --> 00:01:01.063
supporting the man,

00:01:01.682 --> 00:01:04.445
no matter how challenging and undesirable

00:01:04.486 --> 00:01:05.025
that would be.

00:01:06.174 --> 00:01:09.436
the garden's deadbeats were being served a

00:01:09.516 --> 00:01:11.197
giant slice of reality.

00:01:11.819 --> 00:01:13.640
What I don't think anyone has realized

00:01:13.719 --> 00:01:16.861
prior to our series on returning to the

00:01:16.902 --> 00:01:20.004
garden is that it's Yahweh who caused the

00:01:20.045 --> 00:01:20.745
fall of man.

00:01:21.626 --> 00:01:24.468
And he did so because he grew bored

00:01:24.548 --> 00:01:25.468
with Adam.

00:01:26.088 --> 00:01:29.191
Adam was conceived to work and yet he

00:01:29.631 --> 00:01:29.971
didn't,

00:01:29.990 --> 00:01:31.593
he showed no initiative whatsoever.

00:01:32.293 --> 00:01:34.120
He was supposed to listen and respond

00:01:34.159 --> 00:01:35.986
appropriately, but he didn't.

00:01:36.930 --> 00:01:37.350
He was...

00:01:38.694 --> 00:01:40.614
specifically designed to be observant

00:01:40.655 --> 00:01:43.176
because Yahweh wanted him to earn the

00:01:43.236 --> 00:01:46.117
right such that he could be trusted to

00:01:46.137 --> 00:01:48.496
be taken out of the garden and explore

00:01:48.518 --> 00:01:49.957
the universe with God.

00:01:50.597 --> 00:01:54.078
And yet he didn't seem to have any

00:01:54.118 --> 00:01:57.019
interest in that as well.

00:01:57.620 --> 00:02:00.980
And so it became exceedingly boring for

00:02:01.040 --> 00:02:01.301
God.

00:02:02.361 --> 00:02:04.682
found man to be uninteresting, uninvolved,

00:02:04.882 --> 00:02:06.162
and unreliable,

00:02:06.643 --> 00:02:09.104
and therefore God specifically caused the

00:02:09.123 --> 00:02:09.584
fall of man.

00:02:09.743 --> 00:02:14.645
And as we have gone through this story,

00:02:14.705 --> 00:02:16.507
we have come to realize many things,

00:02:16.667 --> 00:02:17.747
such as the fact that

00:02:18.584 --> 00:02:21.066
The two trees in the garden are the

00:02:21.105 --> 00:02:22.026
stars of the show.

00:02:22.066 --> 00:02:23.546
It's the Tree of Lives and the Tree

00:02:23.586 --> 00:02:24.068
of Knowledge.

00:02:24.527 --> 00:02:26.329
Most of the attention in this particular

00:02:26.368 --> 00:02:29.191
episode was on the Tree of Knowledge.

00:02:29.771 --> 00:02:32.432
And these two trees represent the same two

00:02:32.473 --> 00:02:35.034
individuals that were highlighted earlier

00:02:35.354 --> 00:02:37.137
in the Torah in the first chapter.

00:02:37.176 --> 00:02:38.758
This is now the second and third.

00:02:39.798 --> 00:02:42.120
And they were presented as the greater and

00:02:42.159 --> 00:02:43.020
lesser luminaries.

00:02:43.080 --> 00:02:44.901
Now they are the Tree of Lives and

00:02:44.942 --> 00:02:46.402
the Tree of Knowledge.

00:02:47.048 --> 00:02:48.710
We also determined that the Choter,

00:02:48.729 --> 00:02:50.031
which is one of the most interesting

00:02:50.070 --> 00:02:50.611
prophecies,

00:02:50.671 --> 00:02:52.593
probably the single most interesting

00:02:52.633 --> 00:02:54.836
prophecy pursuant to our time,

00:02:56.799 --> 00:03:00.862
taking the entire fourteenth proverb and

00:03:00.902 --> 00:03:04.927
the entire eleventh chapter of Yahshua to

00:03:04.987 --> 00:03:07.030
explain His purpose and His unique

00:03:07.069 --> 00:03:07.509
position.

00:03:08.953 --> 00:03:11.955
that the Chödr is in fact the tree

00:03:12.155 --> 00:03:12.835
of knowledge,

00:03:12.854 --> 00:03:15.836
that there is nothing that differentiates

00:03:15.896 --> 00:03:17.336
them at all.

00:03:18.538 --> 00:03:20.959
So there are a lot of interesting

00:03:21.038 --> 00:03:21.498
insights.

00:03:21.840 --> 00:03:24.681
We were able to deduce the fact that

00:03:25.741 --> 00:03:28.823
Chawa was created to be supportive of man,

00:03:28.883 --> 00:03:30.003
helping the man.

00:03:30.644 --> 00:03:32.104
And yet she turned out to be a

00:03:32.145 --> 00:03:33.465
hindrance to him.

00:03:34.125 --> 00:03:36.705
So it is a very interesting story.

00:03:36.846 --> 00:03:39.387
And the very fact that God now has

00:03:39.667 --> 00:03:41.647
escorted them out of the garden,

00:03:41.668 --> 00:03:43.427
he's having his last conversation with

00:03:43.448 --> 00:03:43.609
them,

00:03:44.808 --> 00:03:47.650
tells us that God was going to give

00:03:47.889 --> 00:03:50.751
us as humans, humans with a nesama,

00:03:50.770 --> 00:03:51.531
with a conscience,

00:03:52.391 --> 00:03:53.611
six thousand years to get our act

00:03:53.632 --> 00:03:53.972
together.

00:03:53.991 --> 00:03:56.112
And over the course of six thousand years,

00:03:56.152 --> 00:03:58.294
God expected that there would be someone

00:03:58.334 --> 00:03:59.174
who would come to

00:04:00.936 --> 00:04:02.756
appreciate what he was saying,

00:04:02.776 --> 00:04:03.456
who would listen to him,

00:04:03.736 --> 00:04:05.717
who would respond accordingly,

00:04:05.776 --> 00:04:08.437
who could be counted upon to do what

00:04:08.518 --> 00:04:10.138
needed to be done, who,

00:04:10.617 --> 00:04:12.658
when he makes a mistake or falls,

00:04:13.218 --> 00:04:16.298
would get back up and demonstrate that he

00:04:16.338 --> 00:04:17.259
could be trusted,

00:04:17.920 --> 00:04:19.300
and that there would be someone

00:04:19.420 --> 00:04:20.680
extraordinarily observant.

00:04:20.759 --> 00:04:22.620
That's why he is called the Nakkar,

00:04:22.680 --> 00:04:23.781
the observant foreigner,

00:04:24.380 --> 00:04:26.701
and that this individual would call many

00:04:26.742 --> 00:04:26.982
more

00:04:27.682 --> 00:04:30.343
back to yahweh and that collectively we

00:04:30.362 --> 00:04:33.303
would end up in a situation where we're

00:04:33.384 --> 00:04:34.783
invited back into the garden we have a

00:04:34.843 --> 00:04:37.305
thousand years now uh at least with a

00:04:37.384 --> 00:04:40.466
select few to get our act together and

00:04:40.526 --> 00:04:43.887
demonstrate to yahweh that we are in fact

00:04:44.327 --> 00:04:45.048
deserving of

00:04:45.591 --> 00:04:46.973
being able to explore the universe with

00:04:46.992 --> 00:04:47.112
him.

00:04:47.653 --> 00:04:51.377
And in this regard, Gan Eden and Sukkah,

00:04:51.596 --> 00:04:55.560
the seventh of Yahweh's Moed Mikra,

00:04:56.120 --> 00:04:56.961
are coterminous.

00:04:57.161 --> 00:04:59.302
Sukkah is about bringing us back to the

00:04:59.322 --> 00:04:59.682
garden.

00:04:59.762 --> 00:05:01.584
And in year six thousand Yahweh,

00:05:01.605 --> 00:05:02.706
which is twenty thirty three,

00:05:03.125 --> 00:05:04.226
just eight years from now,

00:05:04.406 --> 00:05:07.129
we're having this opportunity again for

00:05:07.149 --> 00:05:09.851
this mortal remnant of Israel to be

00:05:09.891 --> 00:05:11.173
allowed back into the garden.

00:05:11.735 --> 00:05:14.055
to demonstrate that we can do better than

00:05:14.175 --> 00:05:16.798
Adam did, six thousand years ago,

00:05:16.877 --> 00:05:18.918
and thereby earned Yahweh's trust.

00:05:20.379 --> 00:05:22.060
So as we consider the following

00:05:22.100 --> 00:05:22.641
assessment,

00:05:22.701 --> 00:05:24.603
